title: For Sale/Trade:  CCW Class March 15
postcontent:
Thank you for your interest in taking my Concealed Carry Handgun Course. 
Things to Know:
•	The class will start at 9:00 am sharp and last until 6:00pm
•	The class will be held at Hope Mills Recreation Center 5770 Rockfish RD Hope Mills, NC 28348.
•	The range is off site about 15 miles from the Recreation center.  We will break around 12 for the qualification.
Things you should Bring:
•	An Open Mind and Willingness to Learn
•	Notebook and a pen 
•	A Handgun and 50 rounds of factory ammo.  (Preferably the handgun you plan to carry)***If you do not have a handgun I have two handguns that can be rented for $20.  This will include the ammo for the handgun****  
•	Eye and Ear Protection ( If you do not have your own I will have some on site for you to purchase)
•	Any snacks or drinks you may want during the course of the day.
•	$50 cash to cover the cost of the class.
•	A holster for your handgun (extra magazines for your handgun are a plus but not necessary)  
Topics that will be Covered:
•	Legal Issues
•	Handgun Safety
•	Handguns/Selection
•	Handgun Fundamentals
•	Marksmanship Fundamentals
•	Carrying Concealed safety Issues
•	Presentation Techniques (Drawing your Handgun)
•	Cleaning and Maintenance
•	Ammunition
•	Proficiency test
After completion of the course and receiving your certificate you can apply to the sheriff’s office in the county you reside. Be sure to take your original training certificate with you when you go to apply. The Sheriff’s office charges $90 for a criminal background check and mental health check. Most Sheriff’s offices require you to pay in cash and EXACT change so make sure you find out ahead of time. Fees can vary somewhat so be sure to check with the Sheriff’s office in your county. If you are approved, your permit will be issued in less than 90 days. It is valid for 5 years. As of January 1,2010, the Sheriff's office is required to send you a renewal notice. The notice will be mailed to the address listed on your permit, so if you move contact the Sheriff's Office with your new address. You must appear at the county sheriff's office and pay the renewal fee. 
******* NO MORE PISTOL PERMITS ********
Under North Carolina Law, the holder of a valid North Carolina Concealed Carry permit can use this permit to purchase handguns in the state of North Carolina. Obtaining a purchase permit is no longer required.

If you have any other questions please feel free to contact me by phone REDACTED  or email  REDACTED
See you on the Range!
Matt Wentzel

title: For Sale:  Glock 21 conversion to 10mm
postcontent:
Have a factory +p Glock 20 10mm and one 10mm magazine. Can be used to shoot 10mm from your Glock 21. Will not work in a Glock 29 or 30.

http://glocktalk.com/forums/showpost.php?p=16838171&postcount=2

A Glock 20 10mm factory barrel actually will function in a G21/G21SF slide and maintain good accuracy. This has been clearly proven in live-fire testing, the results of which are available in multiple cases, for example, Post #79 of the Glock Talk thread titled "Glock 21 conversion to Glock 20?" posted in the General Glocking Forum (Update: the thread has been retired). The O.D. of a G21 and G20 barrel are identical and the barrel lugs are compatible. The same holds true for an aftermarket G20 replacement barrel in the G21 slide (aftermarket G20 barrels from Bar-Sto, KKM Precision, StormLake, Lone Wolf, EFK Fire Dragon and others). While a G20 barrel is a good fit in the critical dimensions, the 10mm barrel chamber hood is narrower than the 45ACP barrel hood by slightly more than .050 inch. The dimensions of a 45-10mm conversion barrel are identical to a G20 10mm factory or aftermarket replacement barrel except that the barrel hood of the conversion barrel is made .050" wider to better fit the 45ACP pistol breechface.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Nikko shotguns for trade on rifles
postcontent:
Nikko 512 with 26" rib vent barrels, top is modified bottom is improved. These were made in kodensha japan in the factory where winchester 101's were made. Incredible shotgun. Could only find one for sale online right now (at 700 and is not all original; the one I own is all original) Nikkos don't pop up often for sale. 

The second Nikko is the N.T.S. (Nikko trap shotgun). 29" rib vent barrels both full choke. This gun is absolutely incredible. Tiger stiped stock and forearm, engraving on absolutely very portion and jeweling on internals to include extractors. Although the 512 was made where the Winchester 101's were this is essentially is a 101 with better wood and parts. Looking online there isn't another one for sale period. This is truely a collector piece and quite rare. 

Neither gun has import marks making them early models. 512 is from early 70's and N.T.S. Most likely from early 60's from research but it's tough as the Nikko company did not keep the same records other companies and the factory was demolished in the early 80's. 

I will gladly meet someone to take a look at either shotgun and send plenty of pictures upon request

title: For Sale/Trade:  Indiana Deer Legal Remington Model 700  350 JR
postcontent:
Two years ago it was illegal to hunt in Indiana with a rifle like this.
 Last year Indiana changed the casing length to 1.8 inches.  I have a gunsmith
 CF Gunworks LLC  that took  the 350 Remington Magnum  and shortened that casing to 1.8 inches
 Which is what this cartridge now is. You can’t  buy this ammo or the gun ,they 
 have to be custom made which is why they are expensive. The .357 and .44 magnums are just another example of Indiana Deer Legal cartridges that you can use. This is a High Powered Rifle that has been modified to meet Indiana specs and requirements . This rifle is 100 % legal to hunt with in Indiana .
Don’t wait for Deer season to decide you want one, you won’t be able to. This is someone’s chance to own
a very nice Indiana Deer Legal High Powered Rifle of which only a hand full are available.

I have a custom built Remington Model 700 That was a 350 Remington Magnum
it has been shortened to 1.8 inch. Indiana Deer Legal casing
the factory barrel has been bedded and set back to shorten the chamber.
It comes with Redding Dies that have been ground to match. 
I have brass and about 30rds of ammo that was made by C F Gunworks.
It is toped off with a leupold 3x9.
This rifle killed 3 deer at over 300yds this past season. It is amazing!!
I would like $1600 with scope or $1400 without.

This Rifle was custom built to Indiana Specs!!!!! And is referred to as a 350 JR
 This cartridge is modeled after the Remington 350 Magnum. They shorten the case
 to 1.8 inches, I took a picture so you can see the cartridge, bullet is 200grn
and clearly meets Indiana guide lines. I hope this helps with the confusion. 
Certain rifles like the .357 magnum or .44 magnum can be bought at walmart
and are perfectly legal. Indiana says you can't go below .357 magnum. This rifle can't
be bought at WalMart they have to be custom made which the price reflects
